   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>To Aelius Eudaimon, strategos of the division of Herakleides, and Serenus, royal secretary of the same division, and ..., village secretary of Kerkesoucha. From Satabous, son of Pa . . ., of the village of Karanis. In accordance with the orders issued by the most illustrious prefect Bassaeus Rufus, I declare the 5 arourai of epibole near the village of Kerkesoucha . . . registered in the name of Isidoros . . ., which I cultivate and which were sown by me, as unwatered for the present . . . year</ab>
         </div>
